ons by other writers on the Creole rebellion; and recent criticism on the novella.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aEnslaved personsxFictionxUnited States. 0aEnslaved personszUnited StatesvFiction. 0aMutinyvFictionxHistoryy19th centuryxUnited StatesxBiographical fiction. 0aMutinyzUnited StatesxHistoryy19th centuryvFiction. 0aSlave insurrectionszUnited StatesxHistoryy19th centuryvFiction. 0aSlave rebellionsvFictionxHistoryy19th centuryxUnited States. 0aSlave rebellionszUnited StatesxHistoryy19th centuryvFiction. 0aSlaveszUnited StatesvFiction. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh1 aKaufman-McKivigan, John R., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aLevine, Robert S., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aStauffer, John, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015z97831106725030 cprintz978030018462440uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/978030021056940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300210569423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300210569/original  a978-3-11-067250-3  Yale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015c2014d2015  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY